{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"queryExists(cancellable:)","extendedModule":"GIO","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:3GIO12FileProtocolPAAE11queryExists11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tF","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"queryExists"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Utility function to check if a particular file exists."}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileProtocol\/queryExists(cancellable:)-4adj8","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"queryExists","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The fallback implementation of this API is using [method"},{"code":"Gio.File.query_info","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and therefore may do blocking I\/O. To asynchronously query the existence"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of a file, use [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.File.query_info_async"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that in many cases it is "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and then execute something based on the outcome of that, because the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"file might have been created or removed in between the operations. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"general approach to handling that is to not check, but just do the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"operation and handle the errors as they come.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As an example of race-free checking, take the case of reading a file,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and if it doesn’t exist, creating it. There are two racy versions: read","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it, and on error create it; and: check if it exists, if not create it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These can both result in two processes creating the file (with perhaps"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a partially written file as the result). The correct approach is to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"always try to create the file with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_create()"},{"type":"text","text":" which will either"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"atomically create the file or fail with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exists"},{"text":" error.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"However, in many cases an existence check is useful in a user interface,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for instance to make a menu item sensitive\/insensitive, so that you don’t"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have to fool users that something is possible and then just show an error","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dialog. If you do this, you should make sure to also handle the errors"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that can happen due to races when you execute the operation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/fileprotocol\/queryexists(cancellable:)-4adj8"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileProtocol"]]},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InputStream":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStream","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInputStream"},{"type":"text","text":" is a base class for implementing streaming input."}],"title":"InputStream","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/inputstream","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"InputStream","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InputStream","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/OutputStream":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"OutputStream","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"code":"GOutputStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a base class for implementing streaming output."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/outputstream","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStream","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OutputStream","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OutputStream","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileProtocol":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileProtocol"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/fileprotocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"FileProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"text":" is a high level abstraction for manipulating files on a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"virtual file system. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GFile"},{"type":"text","text":"s are lightweight, immutable objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that do no I\/O upon creation. It is necessary to understand that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"GFile","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" objects do not represent files, merely an identifier for a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"file. All file content I\/O is implemented as streaming operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(see [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStream","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStream"},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"title":"FileProtocol","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileProtocol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/FileProtocol/queryExists(cancellable:)-4adj8":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Utility function to check if a particular file exists.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"queryExists","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"title":"queryExists(cancellable:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileProtocol\/queryExists(cancellable:)-4adj8","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/fileprotocol\/queryexists(cancellable:)-4adj8"},"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use":{"title":"racy to first check for file existence","url":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"racy to first check for file existence"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time_of_check_to_time_of_use"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"}}}